[
    {
        "text": "This is where the\nmigrants return.",
        "start": 2.75,
        "duration": 2.97
    },
    {
        "text": "Everyone here\nrisked their lives",
        "start": 5.72,
        "duration": 1.44
    },
    {
        "text": "to make it to the United\nStates, and failed.",
        "start": 7.16,
        "duration": 3.76
    },
    {
        "text": "Now, they’re back at\nthis processing center",
        "start": 10.92,
        "duration": 2.15
    },
    {
        "text": "in El Salvador.",
        "start": 13.07,
        "duration": 2.19
    },
    {
        "text": "Many have families\nto receive them.",
        "start": 15.26,
        "duration": 1.46
    },
    {
        "text": "Like Marlene and her\n4-year-old daughter,",
        "start": 22.887,
        "duration": 1.833
    },
    {
        "text": "Sheila.",
        "start": 24.72,
        "duration": 2.374
    },
    {
        "text": "[child shouting]",
        "start": 27.094,
        "duration": 1.488
    },
    {
        "text": "[speaking spanish]",
        "start": 28.582,
        "duration": 1.984
    },
    {
        "text": "William hadn’t seen\nhis daughter in weeks.",
        "start": 34.04,
        "duration": 1.86
    },
    {
        "text": "But he’s willing to send\nSheila back out again,",
        "start": 44.69,
        "duration": 2.79
    },
    {
        "text": "on a dangerous journey.",
        "start": 47.48,
        "duration": 2.49
    },
    {
        "text": "Why?",
        "start": 49.97,
        "duration": 0.9
    },
    {
        "text": "Because it’s more\ndangerous here at home.",
        "start": 50.87,
        "duration": 2.34
    },
    {
        "text": "She can’t even go\nto school safely.",
        "start": 53.21,
        "duration": 2.035
    },
    {
        "text": "[somber music]",
        "start": 55.245,
        "duration": 2.325
    },
    {
        "text": "The migrants are given a quick\nmeal, a pair of new shoes",
        "start": 58.97,
        "duration": 4.1
    },
    {
        "text": "and a ride.",
        "start": 63.07,
        "duration": 0.58
    },
    {
        "text": "Then, they’re thrown\nback into the same world",
        "start": 68.65,
        "duration": 2.46
    },
    {
        "text": "that drove them away.",
        "start": 71.11,
        "duration": 1.68
    },
    {
        "text": "And we’re here to find out\nwhat that world is like.",
        "start": 72.79,
        "duration": 2.22
    },
    {
        "text": "El Salvador has one\nof the highest murder",
        "start": 85.51,
        "duration": 1.8
    },
    {
        "text": "rates in the world.",
        "start": 87.31,
        "duration": 1.68
    },
    {
        "text": "Rival gangs like\nMS-13 and 18th Street",
        "start": 88.99,
        "duration": 2.58
    },
    {
        "text": "have been at war for decades.",
        "start": 91.57,
        "duration": 2.19
    },
    {
        "text": "They work like the\nmafia, extorting money",
        "start": 93.76,
        "duration": 2.22
    },
    {
        "text": "from local businesses,\nfighting for territory",
        "start": 95.98,
        "duration": 2.91
    },
    {
        "text": "and killing with impunity.",
        "start": 98.89,
        "duration": 2.04
    },
    {
        "text": "An average of 18 people are\nkilled or disappear here",
        "start": 100.93,
        "duration": 3.06
    },
    {
        "text": "each day.",
        "start": 103.99,
        "duration": 1.442
    },
    {
        "text": "[gunfire]",
        "start": 105.432,
        "duration": 2.738
    },
    {
        "text": "It all goes back to a civil\nwar that started in 1980.",
        "start": 108.17,
        "duration": 3.51
    },
    {
        "text": "For 12 years,\ncommunist-leaning guerrillas",
        "start": 111.68,
        "duration": 2.28
    },
    {
        "text": "fought against American-backed\nmilitary forces",
        "start": 113.96,
        "duration": 2.52
    },
    {
        "text": "who committed vicious\natrocities against civilians.",
        "start": 116.48,
        "duration": 2.957
    },
    {
        "text": "[tense music]",
        "start": 119.437,
        "duration": 2.385
    },
    {
        "text": "[weeping]",
        "start": 121.822,
        "duration": 2.388
    },
    {
        "text": "Because of the war,\nhundreds of thousands",
        "start": 124.21,
        "duration": 1.89
    },
    {
        "text": "sought asylum in the U.S.",
        "start": 126.1,
        "duration": 2.52
    },
    {
        "text": "It’s there, on the\nstreets of Los Angeles,",
        "start": 128.62,
        "duration": 2.25
    },
    {
        "text": "that many young men were\nintroduced to gang culture.",
        "start": 130.87,
        "duration": 3.64
    },
    {
        "text": "Then, after a peace\ntreaty in 1992,",
        "start": 134.51,
        "duration": 2.54
    },
    {
        "text": "the U.S. deported thousands of\nhardened gang members back.",
        "start": 137.05,
        "duration": 2.7
    },
    {
        "text": "It’s 3 a.m.",
        "start": 157.91,
        "duration": 1.282
    },
    {
        "text": "We’re driving through\none of the most dangerous",
        "start": 159.192,
        "duration": 1.958
    },
    {
        "text": "gang-controlled\nparts of the city.",
        "start": 161.15,
        "duration": 1.416
    },
    {
        "text": "[? chamba ?] is a\nveteran reporter",
        "start": 176.22,
        "duration": 1.49
    },
    {
        "text": "covering gang violence.",
        "start": 177.71,
        "duration": 2.355
    },
    {
        "text": "He asked that we change his\nname and not show his face.",
        "start": 180.065,
        "duration": 2.715
    },
    {
        "text": "The gangs are pervasive,\nand many poor neighborhoods",
        "start": 193.15,
        "duration": 2.81
    },
    {
        "text": "look like this.",
        "start": 195.96,
        "duration": 0.69
    },
    {
        "text": "A local aid group\nintroduced us",
        "start": 212.81,
        "duration": 1.52
    },
    {
        "text": "to Victoria and her\ndaughter, Isabela.",
        "start": 214.33,
        "duration": 2.91
    },
    {
        "text": "They live in hiding,\nrunning a small bakery out",
        "start": 217.24,
        "duration": 2.43
    },
    {
        "text": "of this abandoned house.",
        "start": 219.67,
        "duration": 1.829
    },
    {
        "text": "They’ve had to move three\ntimes in the last three",
        "start": 221.499,
        "duration": 2.041
    },
    {
        "text": "years, and asked us not\nto use their real names.",
        "start": 223.54,
        "duration": 3.93
    },
    {
        "text": "Their problems started\nwith a small squabble",
        "start": 227.47,
        "duration": 1.989
    },
    {
        "text": "between friends.",
        "start": 229.459,
        "duration": 0.666
    },
    {
        "text": "Isabela wanted\nher bracelet back,",
        "start": 248.23,
        "duration": 2.01
    },
    {
        "text": "and that was all it took.",
        "start": 250.24,
        "duration": 1.41
    },
    {
        "text": "She had offended\nthe gangs, which",
        "start": 251.65,
        "duration": 2.13
    },
    {
        "text": "was enough to mark her and\nher entire family for death.",
        "start": 253.78,
        "duration": 4.95
    },
    {
        "text": "So they fled north.",
        "start": 258.73,
        "duration": 1.65
    },
    {
        "text": "At the U.S. border,\nIsabela was caught,",
        "start": 260.38,
        "duration": 2.159
    },
    {
        "text": "and they were\nforced to return.",
        "start": 262.539,
        "duration": 1.291
    },
    {
        "text": "This month, El Salvador\nelected its youngest",
        "start": 277.99,
        "duration": 2.34
    },
    {
        "text": "president ever,\n37-year-old Nayib Bukele,",
        "start": 280.33,
        "duration": 3.93
    },
    {
        "text": "an energetic former\nmayor running",
        "start": 284.26,
        "duration": 1.65
    },
    {
        "text": "against the establishment.",
        "start": 285.91,
        "duration": 1.95
    },
    {
        "text": "It’s the first\ntime in 30 years",
        "start": 287.86,
        "duration": 1.47
    },
    {
        "text": "that the two largest political\nparties failed to take power.",
        "start": 289.33,
        "duration": 3.378
    },
    {
        "text": "[festive music]",
        "start": 292.708,
        "duration": 3.592
    },
    {
        "text": "A clear sign of just\nhow much Salvadorans",
        "start": 296.3,
        "duration": 2.1
    },
    {
        "text": "are craving change.",
        "start": 298.4,
        "duration": 1.412
    },
    {
        "text": "[singing in spanish]",
        "start": 299.812,
        "duration": 1.808
    },
    {
        "text": "We had followed Bukele\non the election trail.",
        "start": 301.62,
        "duration": 3.71
    },
    {
        "text": "Many skeptics say\nhe’s the new face",
        "start": 305.33,
        "duration": 2.04
    },
    {
        "text": "of an old and corrupt\nsystem, but his supporters",
        "start": 307.37,
        "duration": 2.729
    },
    {
        "text": "are inspired.",
        "start": 310.099,
        "duration": 0.541
    },
    {
        "text": "[cheering]",
        "start": 312.674,
        "duration": 2.39
    },
    {
        "text": "But even here, there’s\na fear of the gangs.",
        "start": 321.22,
        "duration": 3.69
    },
    {
        "text": "We see security forces\naccuse this young boy",
        "start": 324.91,
        "duration": 2.58
    },
    {
        "text": "of being a gang lookout.",
        "start": 327.49,
        "duration": 1.0
    },
    {
        "text": "Bukele is making\nambitious promises",
        "start": 332.15,
        "duration": 2.0
    },
    {
        "text": "to weed out corruption\nand reduce inequality.",
        "start": 334.15,
        "duration": 4.32
    },
    {
        "text": "After the rally, we jumped\nin the back of his car.",
        "start": 338.47,
        "duration": 2.832
    },
    {
        "text": "“Hello.”",
        "start": 341.302,
        "duration": 0.5
    },
    {
        "text": "“Hi.",
        "start": 341.802,
        "duration": 0.718
    },
    {
        "text": "The gang violence here seems\nto be the biggest thing",
        "start": 342.52,
        "duration": 2.73
    },
    {
        "text": "that we have uncovered\ntalking to people,",
        "start": 345.25,
        "duration": 1.98
    },
    {
        "text": "and discussing why\nthey’re leaving,",
        "start": 347.23,
        "duration": 2.04
    },
    {
        "text": "why they have problems here.”",
        "start": 349.27,
        "duration": 1.316
    },
    {
        "text": "“It is.”",
        "start": 350.586,
        "duration": 0.499
    },
    {
        "text": "“How are you hoping\nto fight that?”",
        "start": 351.085,
        "duration": 1.458
    },
    {
        "text": "“It’s not a crime problem.",
        "start": 352.543,
        "duration": 2.407
    },
    {
        "text": "It’s a social\nproblem that develops",
        "start": 354.95,
        "duration": 3.59
    },
    {
        "text": "into a crime problem.",
        "start": 358.54,
        "duration": 1.69
    },
    {
        "text": "The real way to\ntackle gang violence",
        "start": 360.23,
        "duration": 2.69
    },
    {
        "text": "is to correct the\nsocial dysfunction",
        "start": 362.92,
        "duration": 3.1
    },
    {
        "text": "that we have in our country,\nwith its social injustice,",
        "start": 366.02,
        "duration": 3.38
    },
    {
        "text": "economical injustice,\nno opportunities,",
        "start": 369.4,
        "duration": 3.17
    },
    {
        "text": "stigmatization.”",
        "start": 372.57,
        "duration": 1.157
    },
    {
        "text": "“It seems like, in\na lot of the things",
        "start": 373.727,
        "duration": 1.583
    },
    {
        "text": "that you’re asking for, it\nrequires a lot of patience.",
        "start": 375.31,
        "duration": 2.7
    },
    {
        "text": "It requires asking\npeople to wait",
        "start": 378.01,
        "duration": 1.83
    },
    {
        "text": "for things to get better.",
        "start": 379.84,
        "duration": 1.65
    },
    {
        "text": "Are you worried about\npeople getting impatient?”",
        "start": 381.49,
        "duration": 2.525
    },
    {
        "text": "“Yes.",
        "start": 384.015,
        "duration": 0.925
    },
    {
        "text": "Probably the most\nimportant thing",
        "start": 384.94,
        "duration": 1.83
    },
    {
        "text": "is not to lose people’s\nfaith in what you are doing.”",
        "start": 386.77,
        "duration": 4.32
    },
    {
        "text": "[ominous music]",
        "start": 391.09,
        "duration": 3.545
    },
    {
        "text": "For now, the fight against\nthe gangs looks like this.",
        "start": 394.635,
        "duration": 3.974
    },
    {
        "text": "[reggaeton music]",
        "start": 398.609,
        "duration": 3.381
    },
    {
        "text": "The police move\nfrom bar to bar,",
        "start": 408.452,
        "duration": 2.218
    },
    {
        "text": "lining up the patrons to\nsearch pockets and phones",
        "start": 410.67,
        "duration": 2.79
    },
    {
        "text": "for any traces\nof gang contact.",
        "start": 413.46,
        "duration": 2.7
    },
    {
        "text": "It’s a show of force,\nand in the end,",
        "start": 416.16,
        "duration": 2.366
    },
    {
        "text": "there are no arrests.",
        "start": 418.526,
        "duration": 0.874
    },
    {
        "text": "The police’s\nheavy-handed tactics",
        "start": 422.75,
        "duration": 1.62
    },
    {
        "text": "haven’t solved the problem,\nand for many people here,",
        "start": 424.37,
        "duration": 3.15
    },
    {
        "text": "it simply adds\nto the atmosphere",
        "start": 427.52,
        "duration": 1.62
    },
    {
        "text": "of violence and intimidation.",
        "start": 429.14,
        "duration": 2.142
    },
    {
        "text": "Back at the\nimmigration center,",
        "start": 434.6,
        "duration": 1.53
    },
    {
        "text": "deportees continue to come in.",
        "start": 436.13,
        "duration": 3.66
    },
    {
        "text": "Among them is Edwin, a\nformer police officer",
        "start": 439.79,
        "duration": 3.69
    },
    {
        "text": "who fled because the gangs\nhad threatened to kill him.",
        "start": 443.48,
        "duration": 2.25
    },
    {
        "text": "Now, he’s headed home.",
        "start": 455.69,
        "duration": 1.83
    },
    {
        "text": "But he won’t stay\nthere for long.",
        "start": 457.52,
        "duration": 2.69
    }
]